Usage: gjob [options] -job NAME (FILENAME | PROJECT)

Description:
  Runs the given job, or project's node locally

  Example: gjob -job 2 @STDB@/folder/project

Options:
  -h[elp]        : displays this help message
  -v[ersion]     : displays version information
  -verbose       : displays additional initialization and run-time information
  -p[ack]        : does not generate empty lines while preprocessing
  -nice NUMBER   : job scheduling priority

Arguments:
  -j[ob] NAME    : job name, or node number
  FILENAME       : text file defining jobs, or
  PROJECT        : project directory
